  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are good examples of websites built using Adobe ColdFusion?",
  "response": "Adobe ColdFusion is a robust web development platform that has been used to build a variety of websites across different industries. While ColdFusion isn't as widely discussed as some other technologies, it has been the backbone of many enterprise-level applications and websites. Here are some notable examples:\n\n### 1. **NASA**\n   - **Website**: [nasa.gov](https://www.nasa.gov)\n   - **Details**: NASA has used ColdFusion for various internal and external web applications, including content management systems and data retrieval systems. The platform's ability to handle large datasets and integrate with other enterprise systems has made it a good fit for NASA's needs.\n\n### 2. **The White House (Formerly)**\n   - **Website**: [whitehouse.gov](https://www.whitehouse.gov)\n   - **Details**: The White House historically used ColdFusion for its website to manage content and handle high traffic. Although the site has since been rebuilt using other technologies, ColdFusion played a significant role in its earlier iterations.\n\n### 3. **The Smithsonian Institution**\n   - **Website**: [si.edu](https://www.si.edu)\n   - **Details**: The Smithsonian Institution has utilized ColdFusion for various projects, including its online collections and educational resources. ColdFusion's ease of integration with databases and its ability to handle complex queries have been beneficial for this cultural institution.\n\n### 4. **MySpace (Formerly)**\n   - **Website**: [myspace.com](https://myspace.com)\n   - **Details**: MySpace, one of the pioneering social networking sites, initially used ColdFusion for its backend. The platform's ability to rapidly develop and deploy features helped MyScale quickly scale up in its early days.\n\n### 5. **The State of Utah**\n   - **Website**: [utah.gov](https://www.utah.gov)\n   - **Details**: The State of Utah has used ColdFusion for various government services and websites. ColdFusion's ability to integrate with existing systems and handle secure transactions has made it a good choice for government applications.\n\n### 6. **Adobe (Internal Applications)**\n   - **Website**: [adobe.com](https://www.adobe.com)\n   - **Details**: Adobe, the company behind ColdFusion, uses the technology for various internal applications and tools. This includes content management systems, intranet portals, and other enterprise-level applications.\n\n### 7. **Major League Baseball (MLB) (Formerly)**\n   - **Website**: [mlb.com](https://www.mlb.com)\n   - **Details**: MLB used ColdFusion for various web applications, including its official website and internal tools. The platform's ability to handle high traffic and integrate with different data sources was beneficial for such a high-profile sports organization.\n\n### 8. **The American Red Cross**\n   - **Website**: [redcross.org](https://www.redcross.org)\n   - **Details**: The American Red Cross has used ColdFusion for various web applications, including donation systems and volunteer management tools. ColdFusion's reliability and ease of use have been key factors in its adoption by this humanitarian organization.\n\n### 9. **The United States Senate (Internal Applications)**\n   - **Website**: [senate.gov](https://www.senate.gov)\n   - **Details**: The United States Senate has used ColdFusion for internal web applications, including systems for managing legislative data and other administrative tasks. The platform's ability to integrate with secure government systems has been a significant advantage.\n\n### 10. **FedEx (Internal Applications)**\n   - **Website**: [fedex.com](https://www.fedex.com)\n   - **Details**: FedEx has used ColdFusion for various internal tools and applications, including logistics and tracking systems. ColdFusion's ability to handle complex business logic and integrate with other enterprise systems has made it a valuable tool for FedEx.\n\nThese examples highlight the versatility and reliability of ColdFusion as a web development platform, particularly in environments that require rapid development, scalability, and integration with existing systems. While the technology landscape continues to evolve, ColdFusion remains a viable option for many organizations.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
